==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tuatara
<hw>Tu`a*ta"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Maori
<ets>tuat⟦agrave⟧ra</ets>; <ets>tua</ets> on the farther side (the back)
+ <ets>tara</ets> spine.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large
iguanalike reptile (<spn>Sphenodon punctatum</spn>) formerly common in
New Zealand, but by 1900 confined to certain islets near the coast. It
reaches a length of two and a half feet, is dark olive-green with small
white or yellowish specks on the sides, and has yellow spines along the
back, except on the neck. It is the only surviving member of the order
<ord>Rhyncocephala</ord>. Also called <altname>tuatera</altname> and
<altname>hatteria</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tuatera</ent>⟦br⟧
